review_blob: Bottle 33cl. Crisp yellow coulour. Fruity but nicely balanced by bitterness. Great very cold on a hot day.

Bottle at home. Nice bitter ipa, rounded with a hint of passion fruit. Bitter aftertaste along the sides of the tongue that makes your mouth water and long for another mouthfull. Full mousse with a cloudy dark yellow colouring.

Session bitter with a light bitter aftertaste. Paired nicely with a risotto. Nice malty taste. Little head. Pours a light golden colour. Too little depth and complexity for my liking. Good for a hot day Id imagine.
Une bonne witbier citronne. Couleur blanche, clair. Gout de cardamom. Une blanche dt de qualite. Trs agreable en accompangant un curry !
Aroma : grassy, herbs. Appearance: pale, clear, minimal head. Taste: watery, sweet hops. Palate :light body, thin feel, flat, ... Not a lot to write home about to be honest.
